The paper deals with word embeddings and their evaluation in the context of digital humanities, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of various embedding techniques and the evaluation of their performance on different tasks suggest a focus on deep learning (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The creation and evaluation of datasets also suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
